{
  "stem": "3341.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they named trustees in every business, in every Jewish firm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The beginning started with the big firms, and we were in the first category of the larger firms.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we were between the first dozen of leading shops in Bratislava who got trustees-- non-Jewish trustees.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They had a special name for it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I can't translate it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And these trustees were usually, or in many cases, women, which is unusual.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can explain it now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The big bosses, either in the new movement of Slovakian guards-- which was like SS-- there were in Germany, as you know, two militaristic powers-- the Wehrmacht, which was the regular army, and then there was the SS, which was the special army of Hitler, and the SS were also having influence in every country which they occupied, like in Czechoslovakia or Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The local Germans formed immediately-- they couldn't form the army, because the army was officially Slovakian National Army.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the second army was the SA-- the SA.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were National Socialist Army of Germans-- the German nationals, all right?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were the most dangerous ones.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So usually, these people who were-- who got suddenly the power, they were captains, and there were militaristic distinctions-- their wives got, as a reward, these very lucrative positions in the Jewish businesses.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We knew about it, because we were-- my brother, who was the manager of our firm, he was of the generation of the 34-- between 30 and 40 years of age.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that the new crop of the new administrators-- the non-Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But he went to school with almost any of them, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he knew the Minister of Justice, his colleague from the high school, or from the university.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
